HEADWORD: Lineage
<hw>Lin"e*age</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧n"⟦esl⟧*⟦asl⟧j; 48)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[OE. <ets>linage</ets>, F. <ets>lignage</ets>, fr. L.
<ets>linea</ets> line. See 3d <er>Line</er>.]</ety> <def>Descent in a
line from a common progenitor; progeny; race; descending line of
offspring or ascending line of parentage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Both the <qex>lineage</qex> and the certain sire⟦br⟧
From which I sprung, from me are hidden yet.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lineal</ent>⟦br⟧
